Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper focuses on the characterization of a specific type of probabilistic model, namely monotone unidimensional latent variable models. The authors discuss the properties and limitations of these models, as well as their applications in various fields such as psychology and education. The paper does not involve any other sub-categories of AI such as Case Based, Genetic Algorithms, Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning, Rule Learning, or Theory.
